        <item>
            <title>0.8.2</title>
            <pubDate>Thu, 23 Jul 2026 15:15:49 +0200</pubDate>
            <sparkle:version>802</sparkle:version>
            <sparkle:shortVersionString>0.8.2</sparkle:shortVersionString>
            <sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>14.0</sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>
            <sparkle:hardwareRequirements>arm64</sparkle:hardwareRequirements>
            <description><![CDATA[<h2>Jarvis 0.8.2</h2>
<p><b>Fixes the crash on quit.</b> If Telegram was connected, quitting Jarvis
could crash at the very last moment — after your data was already safe, but
noisily. It turned out to be a second, separate way the same Telegram engine
teardown could be raced: this one only on app exit, which is why 0.8.1 didn't
catch it. Jarvis now winds the Telegram engine down cleanly before quitting,
in every order of events, and both shutdown paths are covered by tests.</p>
<p>Quitting stays instant if Telegram isn't connected, and adds at most a
brief moment when it is.</p>
]]></description>
